{{Quote|It was great to be a part of something that was so obviously going to become iconic. The decision to join the cast was not mine, but as an actor, my main motivation to work on the show, at least initially, was money. Who knows which projects will ultimately become fun to be a part of, and take you beyond the purely financial reward.|John Stocker, on working on ''Star Wars: Droids''|<ref name="Interview">{{WebCite|url=https://starwarsinterviews.com/animated-series/john-stocker-vlix|text=John Stocker (Vlix)|author=[[Dennis Pellegrom]]|date=2010-08|work=[[Star Wars Interviews]]|archivedate=20230205205501|nolive=1}}</ref>}}
'''John Stocker''' (born [[August 13]], [[1940s#1947|1947]]) is a [[Wikipedia:Canada|Canadian]] voice actor who provided the voice of several villains on the [[Nelvana]] ''[[Star Wars]]'' television show [[Star Wars: Droids: The Adventures of R2-D2 and C-3PO|''Star Wars Droids'']], including [[Ko Zatec-Cha]], as well as [[Sollag Den]] and [[Greej]]. He was also a vocal regular in the animated [[Ewoks (television series)|''Ewoks'']] series, as [[Widdle Warrick/Legends|Widdle Warrick]], plus such episodic roles as [[Mooth]], [[Hoom]], and the [[Dulok/Legends|Dulok]] scout.

Outside of the ''Star Wars'' universe, Stocker's other animated voice roles include Beastly in ''Care Bears'', Basil in ''Babar'', Bugsy in ''Dog City'', Toad and Mouser in ''Super Mario Bros.'', and Father Cat in ''Richard Scarry''. He was also a voice director on ''Sailor Moon'', ''Medabots'' and ''Beyblade''. In the Bakugan anime series as he voiced characters like Naga and Zenoheld.

